Content: [telegram] <Edward_CM> Seeing the convo above. This has been a concern of mine too. Not enough demand for KMD because there aren't enough needs for it like ETH or BNB. JL777 article is great, but in my mind I just don't see 5k KMD or trading pairs on low volume exchanges as creating enough of a network effect. Even the dex won't require KMD for swaps if I recall. I appreciate the philosophy and am still bullish, just not as bullish as I would be with slightly more use of the coin. Doesn't have to be a tax, but maybe creating some more services people can voluntarily utilize if they want and make them use KMD. It's just not right to see so many lesser projects above Komodo on the cmc rankings and it's mainly due to market making and other stuff we could improve on I guess.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <DigitalNinjaa> We have not seen anything like komodo in the market place to date. We do not know what will happen if 1000 projects build on the kmd platform. We do however know what happens with the gas model / tax. The best analogy ive seen was bitcoinbennys and that is kmd is like linux. If you make it restrictive people will look for a less restrictive way to get whats needs to be done done. Every successful project built on kmd promotes kmd. I understand the "theres no buying pressure" argument but i think JL is right when it comes to longterm outlook. When i first used eth i was gobsmacked i needed another coin just to use it. Thats a barrier right there.
